<br>
First, why should Mages have to go back to Old World mobs when other casters can enjoy the luxury of the exp in POP?  I started a Mage because a Magician could solo or bring good benefits to a group.  Because of this reason I debated with the game tester before POP came out when everyone wanted to &quot;Wait and See&quot;.  This is a lesson learned. <br>
<br>
&quot;A ounce of Prevention is worth more then a pound of Cure&quot;<br>
<br>
Now, there are some good points here.  I myself feel that the Pet hitpoints should be raised.  The damage Pets do should also be raised by atleast 10 (far ahead of other classes Pets).  Even with Slow, if Pets had current hitpoints, they would not last long enough to kill the mobs.  So it might be a combination of all 3.  Increase Pets hitpoints, raise Pet damage output, and some type of slow.<br>
<br>
I know it is kind of unrealistic but the way the mobs have progressed through expansion is unrealistic also.  We were once the King of Pets....now that line is blurred.  How do we fix what we shouldnt have let happen from the beginning?<br>
