<br>
If you double or triple the Rathe pet's HP, for example, you'ld have ~ 10 to 15k HP on the pet.  Unbuffed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;OMG - Mages have a 10 K pet.  That's NUTS !&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The problem is that many people equate HP to tanking, without realizing how squishy the pets are.  <br>
<br>
A similar argument can be made for defense.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Excuse me, but I just think it's WRONG for a PET to out-tank a BARD!&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Many classes don't understand that i) Pets will NOT tank with a melee in-range PC present and ii) Pets tanking ability is extraordinarily bad, anyway (compared to the past) and iii) that upping hitpoints really doesn't much affect a group dynamic anyway (from the perspective of singles, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>only</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->), because with melee around pets don't take much damage.  <br>
<br>
Upping the hitpoints and defense are good solutions, viable solutions.  However, with the current political climate created in the aftermath of Uber Chanter Soloing, I can see VI stamping this &quot;Denied&quot;.<br>
<br>
Snare and Root are good solutions, viable solutions.  Due to the Sacred Cow effect, I can see VI stamping this &quot;Denied&quot;.<br>
<br>
One could argue that all these things (The proposed one-tick Slow, increased, AC, improved defense) are all just different facets of the same thing, and are in fact equivalent, from the perspective of the effect on Mage soloing, and impact to the game.  Even if that's true, there is still bound to be complaining, because people are very proprietary about their own class talents, descriptions, and perceived role in the game, particularly when it comes to competition which springs from comparative ability.<br>
<br>
The problem is that Mages want to continue to solo.<br>
<br>
The solution is to keep the pets alive in some way, as we do so.<br>
<br>
The question is how to do it without harming class balance, and just as important, without stepping on other class toes and causing an uproar.  We shouldn't underestimate the &quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; effect, in other words.<br>
<br>
The proposed &quot;1-tick-slow&quot; idea is a good one that mitigates the &quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; effect, well.  I don't like the idea of losing a damage shield, either, but on the other hand, it's not a bad bargaining chip.  Get some, give some.<br>
<br>
As for class balance, a counter to the idea that Mages should be able to solo, is that a Mage in a group would be able to off-tank nearly anything, and with the now white-hot Mage DPS, our solo role <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>had</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be eliminated.<br>
<br>
It is this latter I suspect, and it is probable, in my view, that efficient Mage soloing has gone off into the sunset, in PoP, for good.<br>
<br>
Bara<br>
